{"id":"ater","term":"Ater","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Shut; lame. (1.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 2:16\">Ezra 2:16</a>. (2.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Nehemiah 10:17\">Neh. 10:17</a>. (3.) <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 2:42\">Ezra 2:42</a>.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Ezra 2:16","Nehemiah 10:17","Ezra 2:42"]}